{"body": "If the getting started guide is updated this will help the issue.  However I will still argue that this issue is bad enough that's it's worth doing the OS runtime detection.  In fact, I don't really see the harm in simply checking what OS it is, as pull request #4435 did.  A new user is already going to be overwhelmed when starting Rails with all of the new concepts and tools, I'm not really sure even if they did read a note about this in the getting started guide that they'd understand it.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3484352", "created_at": "2012-01-13T18:52:24Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4451#issuecomment-3484352", "updated_at": "2012-01-13T18:52:24Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 4451, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/brentsowers1", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/4425fd396ee43b48235575d5a4427409?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F24168baa55bf5e1e69d49638b3cf15ea.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/received_events", "gravatar_id": "4425fd396ee43b48235575d5a4427409", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "brentsowers1", "type": "User", "id": 218005, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/brentsowers1/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523825ffbd3543c15100ed76"}, "id": 3484352, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4451"}
